<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
    Bus informationThe Royal Hallamshire is served by the 60, 120 and 10 bus services, which stop close to the main hospital buildings.<br/><br/>The Jessop Wing is also served by these services, but in addition is served by the 51, 52 and 95, which stop outside Weston Park Hospital.  Both are a 5 minute walk away from the Jessop Wing.<br/>Road informationThe Royal Hallamshire Hospital is situated close to the city centre and is accessible from the Sheffield Parkway (ring road). The hospital is easy to access by road with good local transport links. <br/><br/>Road maps to the Royal Hallamshire Hospital and Jessop Wing are available at www.sth.nhs.uk/mapsLocal directionThe Royal Hallamshire is part of the central campus of hospitals which is well signposted as 'central hospitals' from all approaches. <br/><br/>The hospital tower block can be seen for miles around Sheffield.<br/><br/>Rail informationSheffield station is 2 miles from the Royal Hallamshire Hospital and the Jessop Wing. The station is connected to the Sheffield Supertram and is linked to Sheffield Interchange by a short covered walkway. Visitors travelling by rail can catch the 60, 120 and 10 bus services from Sheffield Interchange. Please visit www.nationalrail.co.uk for timetable and ticket information.


</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>There is a multi storey car park at the Royal Hallamshire Hospital, which is 5 minutes walk from the Jessop Wing. Parking is limited and we therefore advise that you leave plenty of time before your appointment to find a parking space. <br/><br/>Parking at the Jessop Wing is also very limited.  </p>
